sition: initial initial !important; background-repeat: initial initial !important; " width="15" /></a></div>\r\n			<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ward_Cunningham" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Ward Cunningham" wotsearchprocessed="true">Ward Cunningham</a>, the developer of the first wiki software,&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WikiWikiWeb" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="WikiWikiWeb" wotsearchprocessed="true">WikiWikiWeb</a></div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 19px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; ">\r\n	A&nbsp;<b>wiki</b>&nbsp;(<span class="nowrap" style="white-space: nowrap; "><a href="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/46/En-us-wiki.ogg" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Listen" wotsearchprocessed="true"><img alt="Listen" height="11" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Speakerlink.svg/11px-Speakerlink.svg.png" style="border-top-style: none; border-right-style: none; border-bottom-style: none; border-left-style: none; border-width: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; vertical-align: middle; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; " width="11" /></a><sup style="line-height: 1em; "><span class="IPA" style="font-family: ''Arial Unicode MS'', ''Lucida Sans Unicode''; color: rgb(0, 0, 238); font: normal normal bold 80%/normal sans-serif; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0.1em; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0.1em; "><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:En-us-wiki.ogg" style="text-decoration: none !important; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="File:En-us-wiki.ogg" wotsearchprocessed="true">i</a></span></sup><span class="IPA" style="font-family: ''Arial Unicode MS'', ''Lucida Sans Unicode''; " title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English" style="text-decoration: none !important; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" wotsearchprocessed="true">/</a></span><span class="IPA" style="font-family: ''Arial Unicode MS'', ''Lucida Sans Unicode''; "><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key" style="text-decoration: none !important; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" wotsearchprocessed="true"><span style="border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: initial; " title="primary stress follows">ˈ</span></a></span><span class="IPA" style="font-family: ''Arial Unicode MS'', ''Lucida Sans Unicode''; "><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key" style="text-decoration: none !important; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" wotsearchprocessed="true"><span style="border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: initial; " title="''w'' in ''wind''">w</span></a></span><span class="IPA" style="font-family: ''Arial Unicode MS'', ''Lucida Sans Unicode''; "><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key" style="text-decoration: none !important; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" wotsearchprocessed="true"><span style="border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: initial; " title="short ''i'' in ''bid''">ɪ</span></a></span><span class="IPA" style="font-family: ''Arial Unicode MS'', ''Lucida Sans Unicode''; "><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key" style="text-decoration: none !important; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" wotsearchprocessed="true"><span style="border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: initial; " title="''k'' in ''kind''">k</span></a></span><span class="IPA" style="font-family: ''Arial Unicode MS'', ''Lucida Sans Unicode''; "><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key" style="text-decoration: none !important; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" wotsearchprocessed="true"><span style="border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: initial; " title="''y'' in ''happy''">i</span></a></span><span class="IPA" style="font-family: ''Arial Unicode MS'', ''Lucida Sans Unicode''; " title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English" style="text-decoration: none !important; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" wotsearchprocessed="true">/</a></span></span>&nbsp;<span class="IPA" style="font-family: ''Arial Unicode MS'', ''Lucida Sans Unicode''; " title="English pronunciation respelling"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Pronunciation_respelling_key" style="text-decoration: none !important; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Wikipedia:Pronunciation respelling key" wotsearchprocessed="true"><i><b><span style="font-variant: small-caps; ">wik</span></b>-ee</i></a></span>) is a&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Website" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Website" wotsearchprocessed="true">website</a>&nbsp;whose users can add, modify, or delete its content via a&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_browser" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Web browser" wotsearchprocessed="true">web browser</a>&nbsp;using a simplified&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markup_language" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Markup language" wotsearchprocessed="true">markup language</a>&nbsp;or a&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Online_rich-text_editor" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Online rich-text editor" wotsearchprocessed="true">rich-text editor</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-0" style="line-height: 1em; "><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiki#cite_note-0" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; white-space: nowrap; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " wotsearchprocessed="true">[1]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-Britannica_1-0" style="line-height: 1em; "><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiki#cite_note-Britannica-1" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; white-space: nowrap; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " wotsearchprocessed="true">[2]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-urlEasy_Wiki_Hosting.2C_Scott_Hanselmans_blog.2C_and_Snagging_Screens_2-0" style="line-height: 1em; "><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiki#cite_note-urlEasy_Wiki_Hosting.2C_Scott_Hanselmans_blog.2C_and_Snagging_Screens-2" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; white-space: nowrap; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " wotsearchprocessed="true">[3]</a></sup>&nbsp;Wikis are typically powered by&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiki_software" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Wiki software" wotsearchprocessed="true">wiki software</a>&nbsp;and are often&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collaborative_software" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Collaborative software" wotsearchprocessed="true">created collaboratively</a>&nbsp;by multiple users. Examples include community websites, corporate&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intranet" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Intranet" wotsearchprocessed="true">intranets</a>,&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Knowledge_management" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Knowledge management" wotsearchprocessed="true">knowledge management</a>&nbsp;systems, and&nbsp;<a class="mw-redirect" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Notetaking_software" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Notetaking software" wotsearchprocessed="true">notetaking</a>.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 19px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; ">\r\n	Wikis may serve many different purposes. Some permit control over different functions (levels of access). For example, editing rights may permit changing, adding or removing material. Others may permit access without enforcing access control. Other rules may also be imposed for organizing content.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 19px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; ">\r\n	<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ward_Cunningham" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Ward Cunningham" wotsearchprocessed="true">Ward Cunningham</a>, the developer of the first wiki software,&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WikiWikiWeb" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="WikiWikiWeb" wotsearchprocessed="true">WikiWikiWeb</a>, originally described it as &quot;the simplest online database that could possibly work.&quot;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3" style="line-height: 1em; "><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiki#cite_note-3" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; white-space: nowrap; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " wotsearchprocessed="true">[4]</a></sup>&quot;Wiki&quot; (pronounced&nbsp;<span class="IPA" style="font-family: ''Arial Unicode MS'', ''Lucida Sans Unicode''; " title="Pronunciation in IPA"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_Hawaiian" style="text-decoration: none !important; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Wikipedia:IPA for Hawaiian" wotsearchprocessed="true">[ˈwiti]</a></span>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<span class="IPA" style="font-family: ''Arial Unicode MS'', ''Lucida Sans Unicode''; " title="Pronunciation in IPA"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_Hawaiian" style="text-decoration: none !important; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Wikipedia:IPA for Hawaiian" wotsearchprocessed="true">[ˈviti]</a></span>) is a&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hawaiian_language" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Hawaiian language" wotsearchprocessed="true">Hawaiian</a>&nbsp;word meaning &quot;fast&quot; or &quot;quick&quot;.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4" style="line-height: 1em; "><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiki#cite_note-4" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; white-space: nowrap; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " wotsearchprocessed="true">[5]</a></sup></p>\r\n', 11, 'Старт', 0),
(17, 2, '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-weight: normal; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 0px; overflow-x: hidden; overflow-y: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0.17em; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(170, 170, 170); width: auto; font-size: 19px; font-family: sans-serif; line-height: 19px; ">\r\n	<span class="mw-headline" id="Characteristics">Characteristics</span></h2>\r\n<p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 19px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; ">\r\n	Ward Cunningham and co-author&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bo_Leuf" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Bo Leuf" wotsearchprocessed="true">Bo Leuf</a>, in their book&nbsp;<i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Wiki_Way" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="The Wiki Way" wotsearchprocessed="true">The Wiki Way: Quick Collaboration on the Web</a></i>, described the essence of the Wiki concept as follows:</p>\r\n<ul style="line-height: 19px; list-style-type: square; margin-top: 0.3em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1.6em; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; list-style-image: url(data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAUAAAANCAMAAABW4lS6AAAAGXRFWHRTb2Z0d2FyZQBBZG9iZSBJbWFnZVJlYWR5ccllPAAAAAZQTFRFAFKM////QIUK9QAAAAJ0Uk5T/wDltzBKAAAAGklEQVR42mJgBAEGokgGBjBGBxBxsBqAAAMACHwALd5r8ygAAAAASUVORK5CYII=); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; ">\r\n	<li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em; ">\r\n		A wiki invites all users to edit any page or to create new pages within the wiki Web site, using only a&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vanilla_software" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Vanilla software" wotsearchprocessed="true">plain-vanilla</a>&nbsp;Web browser without any extra&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Browser_extension" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Browser extension" wotsearchprocessed="true">add-ons</a>.</li>\r\n	<li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em; ">\r\n		Wiki promotes meaningful topic associations between different pages by making page link creation almost intuitively easy and showing whether an intended target page exists or not.</li>\r\n	<li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em; ">\r\n		A wiki is not a carefully crafted site for casual visitors. Instead, it seeks to involve the visitor in an ongoing process of creation and collaboration that constantly changes the Web site landscape.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 19px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; ">\r\n	A wiki enables communities to write documents collaboratively, using a simple markup language and a web browser. A single page in a wiki website is referred to as a &quot;wiki page&quot;, while the entire collection of pages, which are usually well interconnected by&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyperlink" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Hyperlink" wotsearchprocessed="true">hyperlinks</a>, is &quot;the wiki&quot;. A wiki is essentially a database for creating, browsing, and searching through information. A wiki allows for non-linear, evolving, complex and networked text, argument and interaction.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-Legal_11-0" style="line-height: 1em; "><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiki#cite_note-Legal-11" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; white-space: nowrap; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " wotsearchprocessed="true">[12]</a></sup></p>\r\n<p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 19px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; ">\r\n	A defining characteristic of wiki technology is the ease with which pages can be created and updated. Generally, there is no review before modifications are accepted. Many wikis are open to alteration by the general public without requiring them to register&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User_(computing)" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="User (computing)" wotsearchprocessed="true">user</a>&nbsp;accounts. Many edits can be made in real-time and appear almost instantly online. This can facilitate abuse of the system. Private wiki servers require&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Authentication" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Authentication" wotsearchprocessed="true">user authentication</a>&nbsp;to edit pages, and sometimes even to read them.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 19px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; ">\r\n	<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maged_N._Kamel_Boulos" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Maged N. Kamel Boulos" wotsearchprocessed="true">Maged N. Kamel Boulos</a>, Cito Maramba and&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Wheeler" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Steve Wheeler" wotsearchprocessed="true">Steve Wheeler</a>&nbsp;write that it is the &quot;openness of wikis that gives rise to the concept of &#39;Darwikinism&#39;, which is a concept that describes the &#39;<a class="mw-redirect" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Socially_Darwinian" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Socially Darwinian" wotsearchprocessed="true">socially Darwinian</a>process&#39; that wiki pages are subject to. Basically, because of the openness of wikis and the rapidity with which wiki pages can be edited, the pages undergo a&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_selection" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " title="Natural selection" wotsearchprocessed="true">natural selection</a>&nbsp;process like that which nature subjects to living organisms. &#39;Unfit&#39; sentences and sections are ruthlessly culled, edited and replaced if they are not considered &#39;fit&#39;, which hopefully results in the evolution of a higher quality and more relevant page. Whilst such openness may invite &#39;vandalism&#39; and the posting of untrue information, this same openness also makes it possible to rapidly correct or restore a &#39;quality&#39; wiki page.&quot;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-BMC_12-0" style="line-height: 1em; "><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiki#cite_note-BMC-12" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; white-space: nowrap; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; " wotsearchprocessed="true">[13]</a></sup></p>\r\n', 11, 'Информация', 0);
